  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rehabilitation of Affected Educational Facilities in the Eastern and Southern Aleppo Countryside - Phase 2</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project Summary:

The purpose of this project is to ensure a proper learning environment for girls, boys, and adolescents affected by the crisis by providing sustainable access to protective learning spaces through the rehabilitation of seven damaged public schools in the Eastern and Southern Aleppo countryside.

The school environment divided into teaching and non-teaching spaces, school facilities, and premises. The proposed project goes far beyond to ensure the safety and healthiness of the learning environment to make the school a desirable place for about (3620) direct beneficiaries through rehabilitation of:

a. Teaching Spaces: classrooms (71), computer rooms (2), and laboratories (2).
b. Non-Teaching Spaces: administration rooms (17), WASH facilities with sex-segregated for girls and boys (39), roofs, and corridors.
c. School Facilities and premises: Playground (7), Schoolyard (2), access ramps (7), and boundary fence.

Moreover, this project will work as an entry point for other program interventions as Early Childhood Programme to help pre-school age children to get prepared for school by acquiring basic knowledge. Therefore, (7) Early Childhood rooms will be fitted in line with MoE and EDU sector directions.

Fouadi will implement this education intervention directly in line with MoE standards and EDU sector criteria to address gaps in the educational needs of affected populations scattered in rural conflict-affected areas in the countryside of the Aleppo Governorate where educational needs have not fully met.</narrative>
  </description>
